# Function to read WAV files and create datasets
def create_dataset(clean_paths, noisy_paths, batch_size=64, shuffle=True, audio_length=16000):
#     def load_wav(file_path):
#         # Read in a file
#         audio = tf.io.read_file(file_path)
#         # Decode to tensor
#         audio, _ = tf.audio.decode_wav(audio, desired_channels=1)
#         # Make it mono
#         audio = tf.squeeze(audio, axis=-1)
#         # Pad it to 16128
#         # For some reason this step needs to be VERY explicit
#         audio = tf.pad(audio, paddings=[[0, audio_length - tf.shape(audio)[0]]], mode='CONSTANT', constant_values=0)
#         return audio 
    def load_wav(file_path):
        # Read in a file
        audio = tf.io.read_file(file_path)
        # Decode to tensor
        audio, _ = tf.audio.decode_wav(audio, desired_channels=1)
        # Make it mono
        audio = tf.squeeze(audio, axis=-1)
        # Pad or truncate it to 16000
        audio = tf.cond(tf.shape(audio)[0] < audio_length,
                        # If less than 16000 pad to 16000
                        lambda: tf.pad(audio, paddings=[[0, audio_length - tf.shape(audio)[0]]], mode='CONSTANT', constant_values=0),
                        # If more than 16000 truncate the dead space
                        lambda: audio[:audio_length])
        return audio 

    # Get a list of paths pointing to individual samples wav files
    clean_dataset = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices(clean_paths)
    # replace those paths with the audio actually stored there
    clean_dataset = clean_dataset.map(load_wav)
    # Get a list of paths pointing to individual samples wav files
    noisy_dataset = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices(noisy_paths)
    # replace those paths with the audio actually stored there
    noisy_dataset = noisy_dataset.map(load_wav)
    # Zip the clean and noisy datasets together
    dataset = tf.data.Dataset.zip((noisy_dataset, clean_dataset))
    # Shuffly the data so all the same samples arent stuck together
    if shuffle:
        dataset = dataset.shuffle(100)
    # Batch the data and drop the remainders so every batch is the same
    dataset = dataset.batch(batch_size, drop_remainder=True)
    return dataset

# Function to get the length of audio files
def get_audio_length(paths):
    audio_lengths = []
    for path in tqdm(paths):
        audio = tf.io.read_file(path)
        audio, _ = tf.audio.decode_wav(audio, desired_channels=1)
        audio_lengths.append(audio.shape[0])
    return audio_lengths
# Paths to train and test folders
train_clean_paths = glob.glob('WavesFromSpecs/y_train/*.wav')

test_noisy_paths = glob.glob('WavesFromSpecs/test/*.wav')

test_dataset = create_dataset(test_clean_paths, test_noisy_paths, batch_size=16, audio_length=rate) # 16 one second sample batches

# Define the model
batching_size = rate
inp = Input(shape=(batching_size, 1))
c1 = Conv1D(2, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(inp)
c2 = Conv1D(4, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c1)
c3 = Conv1D(8, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c2)
c4 = Conv1D(16, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c3)
c5 = Conv1D(32, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c4)

dc1 = Conv1DTranspose(32, 32, 1, padding='same')(c5)
conc = Concatenate()([c5, dc1])
dc2 = Conv1DTranspose(16, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
conc = Concatenate()([c4, dc2])
dc3 = Conv1DTranspose(8, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
conc = Concatenate()([c3, dc3])
dc4 = Conv1DTranspose(4, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
conc = Concatenate()([c2, dc4])
dc5 = Conv1DTranspose(2, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
conc = Concatenate()([c1, dc5])
dc6 = Conv1DTranspose(1, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
conc = Concatenate()([inp, dc6])
dc7 = Conv1DTranspose(1, 32, 1, padding='same', activation='linear')(conc)

model = tf.keras.models.Model(inp, dc7)
model.summary()

5X Filters Model¶

Create a model with 5 Times the number of filters to test if the models performance is being constrained by a lack of dimensionality from filters.

input_size1d = (rate,1)
inp = Input(shape=(input_size1d))
filterX =5
c1 = Conv1D(2*filterX, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(inp)
c2 = Conv1D(4*filterX, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c1)
c3 = Conv1D(8*filterX, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c2)
c4 = Conv1D(16*filterX, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c3)
c5 = Conv1D(32*filterX, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c4)

dc1 = Conv1DTranspose(32*filterX, 32, 1, padding='same')(c5)
conc = Concatenate()([c5, dc1])
dc2 = Conv1DTranspose(16*filterX, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
conc = Concatenate()([c4, dc2])
dc3 = Conv1DTranspose(8*filterX, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
conc = Concatenate()([c3, dc3])
dc4 = Conv1DTranspose(4*filterX, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
conc = Concatenate()([c2, dc4])
dc5 = Conv1DTranspose(2*filterX, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
conc = Concatenate()([c1, dc5])
dc6 = Conv1DTranspose(1*filterX, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
conc = Concatenate()([inp, dc6])
dc7 = Conv1DTranspose(1, 32, 1, padding='same', activation='linear')(conc)

un_1d_big = tf.keras.models.Model(inp, dc7)
un_1d_big.summary()

for i in range(3):
    # Define the model
    file_length = rate
    batch_size = 16
    filterX =0.5
    # input_size1d = (1,16128)
    input_size1d = (rate,1)
    inp = Input(shape=(input_size1d))
    c1 = Conv1D(2*filterX, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(inp)
    c2 = Conv1D(4*filterX, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c1)
    c3 = Conv1D(8*filterX, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c2)
    c4 = Conv1D(16*filterX, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c3)
    c5 = Conv1D(32*filterX, 32, 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c4)

    dc1 = Conv1DTranspose(32*filterX, 32, 1, padding='same')(c5)
    conc = Concatenate()([c5, dc1])
    dc2 = Conv1DTranspose(16*filterX, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([c4, dc2])
    dc3 = Conv1DTranspose(8*filterX, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([c3, dc3])
    dc4 = Conv1DTranspose(4*filterX, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([c2, dc4])
    dc5 = Conv1DTranspose(2*filterX, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([c1, dc5])
    dc6 = Conv1DTranspose(1, 32, 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([inp, dc6])
    dc7 = Conv1DTranspose(1, 32, 1, padding='same', activation='linear')(conc)

    un_1d_small = tf.keras.models.Model(inp, dc7)
    # un_1d_base.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(0.002),loss='mse',metrics=['mae','accuracy']
    un_1d_small.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(0.001),loss='mse',metrics=['mae','accuracy'])
    historysmall = un_1d_small.fit(train_dataset,epochs=20)
    un_1d_small.save(f"un_1d_small{i}.keras")
    K.clear_session()

%matplotlib inline
def load_wav(file_path):
    audio_length = 16000
    # Read in a file
    audio = tf.io.read_file(file_path)
    # Decode to tensor
    audio, _ = tf.audio.decode_wav(audio, desired_channels=1)
    # Make it mono
    audio = tf.squeeze(audio, axis=-1)
    # Pad or truncate it to 16000
    audio = tf.cond(tf.shape(audio)[0] < audio_length,
                    # If less than 16000 pad to 16000
                    lambda: tf.pad(audio, paddings=[[0, audio_length - tf.shape(audio)[0]]], mode='CONSTANT', constant_values=0),
                    # If more than 16000 truncate the dead space
                    lambda: audio[:audio_length])
    return audio

def amplifyMagnitudeByLog(d):
    return 188.301 * math.log10(d + 1)

def weakenAmplifiedMagnitude(d):
    return math.pow(10, d/188.301)-1

def generateLinearScale(magnitudePixels, phasePixels, magnitudeMin, magnitudeMax, phaseMin, phaseMax):
    height = magnitudePixels.shape[0]
    width = magnitudePixels.shape[1]
    magnitudeRange = magnitudeMax - magnitudeMin
    phaseRange = phaseMax - phaseMin
    rgbArray = np.zeros((height, width, 3), 'uint8')
    
    for w in range(width):
        for h in range(height):
            magnitudePixels[h,w] = (magnitudePixels[h,w] - magnitudeMin) / (magnitudeRange) * 255 * 2
            magnitudePixels[h,w] = amplifyMagnitudeByLog(magnitudePixels[h,w])
            phasePixels[h,w] = (phasePixels[h,w] - phaseMin) / (phaseRange) * 255
            red = 255 if magnitudePixels[h,w] > 255 else magnitudePixels[h,w]
            green = (magnitudePixels[h,w] - 255) if magnitudePixels[h,w] > 255 else 0
            blue = phasePixels[h,w]
            rgbArray[h,w,0] = int(red)
            rgbArray[h,w,1] = int(green)
            rgbArray[h,w,2] = int(blue)
    return rgbArray

def recoverLinearScale(rgbArray, magnitudeMin, magnitudeMax, phaseMin, phaseMax):
    width = rgbArray.shape[1]
    height = rgbArray.shape[0]
    print(phaseMax,phaseMin)
    magnitudeVals = rgbArray[:,:,0].astype(float) + rgbArray[:,:,1].astype(float)
    phaseVals = rgbArray[:,:,2].astype(float)
    phaseRange = phaseMax - phaseMin
    magnitudeRange = magnitudeMax - magnitudeMin
    
    for w in range(width):
        for h in range(height):
            phaseVals[h,w] = (phaseVals[h,w] / 255 * phaseRange) + phaseMin
            magnitudeVals[h,w] = weakenAmplifiedMagnitude(magnitudeVals[h,w])
            magnitudeVals[h,w] = (magnitudeVals[h,w] / (255*2) * magnitudeRange) + magnitudeMin
    return magnitudeVals, phaseVals
def generateSpectrogramForWave(signal):
    global magnitudeMin
    global magnitudeMax
    global phaseMin
    global phaseMax
    buffer = np.zeros(int(signal.size + WINDOW_STEP - (signal.size % WINDOW_STEP)))
    buffer[0:len(signal)] = signal
    height = int(FFT_LENGTH / 2 + 1)
    width = int(len(buffer) / (WINDOW_STEP) - 1)
    magnitudePixels = np.zeros((height, width))
    phasePixels = np.zeros((height, width))

    for w in range(width):
        buff = np.zeros(FFT_LENGTH)
        stepBuff = buffer[w*WINDOW_STEP:w*WINDOW_STEP + WINDOW_LENGTH]
        # apply hanning window
        stepBuff = stepBuff * np.hanning(WINDOW_LENGTH)
        buff[0:len(stepBuff)] = stepBuff
        #buff now contains windowed signal with step length and padded with zeroes to the end
        fft = np.fft.rfft(buff)
        for h in range(len(fft)):
            #print(buff.shape)
            magnitude = math.sqrt(fft[h].real**2 + fft[h].imag**2)
            if magnitude > magnitudeMax:
                magnitudeMax = magnitude 
            if magnitude < magnitudeMin:
                magnitudeMin = magnitude 

            phase = math.atan2(fft[h].imag, fft[h].real)
            if phase > phaseMax:
                phaseMax = phase
            if phase < phaseMin:
                phaseMin = phase
            magnitudePixels[height-h-1,w] = magnitude
            phasePixels[height-h-1,w] = phase
    rgbArray = generateLinearScale(magnitudePixels, phasePixels, magnitudeMin, magnitudeMax, phaseMin, phaseMax)

    img = Image.fromarray(rgbArray, 'RGB')
    return img

Create 0.5X Kernel/Window Model¶

Create a model with half the kernel width of the Base model to test whether the model benefits from analyzing smaller portions of the audio at a time. By decreasing the kernel width the model will capture patterns that occur over smaller periods of time which will hopefully give the model more fundamental patterns to build upon in consequent layers. 10 ms window

for i in range(3):
    # Define the model

    batch_size = 16
    filterX = 1
    windowX = 0.5
    # input_size1d = (1,16128)

    inp = Input(shape=(input_size1d))
    c1 = Conv1D(2*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(inp)

    c3 = Conv1D(8*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c2)
    c4 = Conv1D(16*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c3)
    c5 = Conv1D(32*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c4)

    dc1 = Conv1DTranspose(32*filterX, int(32*windowX), 1, padding='same')(c5)

    dc2 = Conv1DTranspose(16*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, padding='same')(conc)

    dc3 = Conv1DTranspose(8*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([c3, dc3])
    dc4 = Conv1DTranspose(4*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, padding='same')(conc)

Create and Train 2X Kernel Model¶

Create a model with twice the kernel width of the Base model to test whether the model benefits from analyzing larger portions of the audio at a time. By increasing the kernel width the model will capture patterns that occur over larger periods of time which will hopefully allow the model to capture patterns closer to natural speech like the "t" sound which takes place over roughly 50-100ms. 40ms window

for i in range(3):
    # Define the model
    file_length = rate
    batch_size = 16
    filterX = 1
    windowX = 2
    # input_size1d = (1,16128)
    input_size1d = (rate,1)
    inp = Input(shape=(input_size1d))
    c1 = Conv1D(2*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(inp)
    c2 = Conv1D(4*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c1)
    c3 = Conv1D(8*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c2)
    c4 = Conv1D(16*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c3)
    c5 = Conv1D(32*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c4)

    dc1 = Conv1DTranspose(32*filterX, int(32*windowX), 1, padding='same')(c5)
    conc = Concatenate()([c5, dc1])
    dc2 = Conv1DTranspose(16*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([c4, dc2])
    dc3 = Conv1DTranspose(8*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([c3, dc3])

    conc = Concatenate()([c2, dc4])

    dc7 = Conv1DTranspose(1, int(32*windowX), 1, padding='same', activation='linear')(conc)

    un_1d_doublewin.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(0.001),loss='mse',metrics=['mae','accuracy'])

Create and Train 5X Kernel Model¶

Create a model with five times the kernel width of the Base model to test whether the model benefits from analyzing larger portions of the audio at a time. By increasing the kernel width the model will capture patterns that occur over larger periods of time which will hopefully allow the model to capture patterns closer to natural speech like the "t" sound which takes place over roughly 50-100ms. 100 ms window

In [28]:
for i in range(3):
    # Define the model
    file_length = rate
    batch_size = 16
    filterX = 1
    windowX = 5
    # input_size1d = (1,16128)
    input_size1d = (rate,1)
    inp = Input(shape=(input_size1d))
    c1 = Conv1D(2*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(inp)
    c2 = Conv1D(4*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c1)
    c3 = Conv1D(8*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c2)
    c4 = Conv1D(16*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c3)
    c5 = Conv1D(32*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c4)

    dc1 = Conv1DTranspose(32*filterX, int(32*windowX), 1, padding='same')(c5)
    conc = Concatenate()([c5, dc1])
    dc2 = Conv1DTranspose(16*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([c4, dc2])
    dc3 = Conv1DTranspose(8*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([c3, dc3])
    dc4 = Conv1DTranspose(4*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([c2, dc4])
    dc5 = Conv1DTranspose(2*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([c1, dc5])
    dc6 = Conv1DTranspose(1, int(32*windowX), 2, padding='same')(conc)
    conc = Concatenate()([inp, dc6])
    dc7 = Conv1DTranspose(1, int(32*windowX), 1, padding='same', activation='linear')(conc)

    un_1d_5win = tf.keras.models.Model(inp, dc7)
    # un_1d_base.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(0.002),loss='mse',metrics=['mae','accuracy']
    un_1d_5win.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(0.001),loss='mse',metrics=['mae','accuracy'])
    history5 = un_1d_5win.fit(train_dataset,epochs=20)
    un_1d_5win.save(f"un_1d_5win{i}.keras")
    K.clear_session()

for i in range(3):
    # Define the model
    file_length = rate
    batch_size = 16
    filterX = 1
    windowX = 1
    # input_size1d = (1,16128)
    input_size1d = (rate,1)

    c2 = Conv1D(4*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c1)
    c3 = Conv1D(8*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c2)
    c4 = Conv1D(16*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c3)
    c5 = Conv1D(32*filterX, int(32*windowX), 2, 'same', activation='relu')(c4)

    dc1 = Conv1DTranspose(32*filterX, int(32*windowX), 1, padding='same')(c5)
    conc = Concatenate()([c5, dc1])

    un_1d_5e.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(0.001),loss='mse',metrics=['mae','accuracy'])

Create and Train a Model with AdaGrad Optimizer¶

Recreate the Base model with an AdaGrad optimizer and 2.5 times as many epochs as the AdaGrad has shown in other projects We've worked on to train well but take significantly longer than other solvers such as Adam.
